<item>
            <title>[LU-12463] Do not report &quot;over quota&quot; when project is below soft limit and quotas are no longer enabled.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12463</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A project was reported over quota, after quota enforcement was disabled and sufficient block files were deleted.&#160; It seems that after enforcement is disabled, deleting files won&apos;t change the quota reporting state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce this problem:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;enable quota enforcement&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;define a project quota with soft and hard limits&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;create enough data in project to exceed soft limit&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;disable quota enforcement&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;delete files from project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;After these steps, the project quota will report exceeded soft quota even though files were deleted from project and usage is under soft limit.&#160; This state will continue until quota enforcement is re-enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that it should not be necessary to re-enforce project quotas to have the project again display as within quota.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your consideration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
